(41, 10, 18, 45, 3, 12, 12, 'none good but one, that is, God', 'Goodness and Human Nature', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of goodness and the lack thereof in humanity. Mark 10:18 states that only God is good, while Romans 3:12 asserts that there is none that doeth good, highlighting a shared theme of human unworthiness.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
