(41, 10, 18, 62, 4, 16, 16, 'none good but one, that is, God', 'Goodness and Love of God', 'This connection highlights the nature of God as both good and loving. In Mark, Jesus emphasizes that only God is good, while 1 John affirms that God is love, suggesting a deep relationship between God''s goodness and love.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 18, 43, 5, 41, 44, 'none good but one, that is, God', 'Honor and Goodness Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of seeking honor from God versus human recognition. In Mark, Jesus emphasizes that only God is good, while in John, He points out that people seek honor from one another rather than from God.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 18, 59, 1, 17, 17, 'none good but one, that is, God', 'Connection of Goodness in Scripture', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of goodness, with Mark 10:18 stating that only God is good, while James 1:17 declares that every good gift comes from God. This connection highlights the source of goodness as being divine.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
