(41, 10, 19, 59, 2, 11, 11, 'Do not commit adultery', 'Connection of Commandments', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of the commandments, specifically mentioning ''Do not commit adultery'' and ''Do not kill.'' This connection highlights the idea that transgressing any commandment makes one a transgressor of the law.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 19, 40, 19, 17, 19, NULL, 'Connection of Commandments', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of keeping the commandments, listing similar prohibitions and duties. This connection highlights the continuity in Jesus'' teaching regarding moral conduct.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 19, 42, 18, 20, 20, NULL, 'Connection of Commandments in Gospels', 'Both passages emphasize the same commandments, listing similar prohibitions and the call to honor parents. This connection highlights the continuity of moral teachings in the synoptic gospels.', 'parallel', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 19, 46, 6, 7, 9, 'Defraud not', 'Moral Conduct and Defrauding', 'Both passages emphasize moral conduct and the wrongness of defrauding others. Mark 10:19 lists commandments that include not defrauding, while 1 Corinthians 6:7-9 addresses the issue of defrauding brethren, linking the moral implications of both texts.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 19, 5, 5, 16, 24, 'Honour thy father and mother', 'Connection of Commandments', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of moral commandments, listing similar prohibitions against actions like killing, adultery, and stealing. This connection highlights the continuity of ethical teachings from Deuteronomy to the teachings of Jesus.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 20, 26, 33, 31, 32, 'all these have I observed', 'Connection of Obedience and Heart', 'This connection highlights the theme of outward compliance versus inner devotion. Both passages emphasize that mere observance of commandments or words is insufficient without genuine commitment and action from the heart.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 20, 50, 3, 6, 6, 'all these have I observed', 'Righteousness and Law Observance', 'This connection highlights the theme of law observance and personal righteousness. Both passages emphasize a sense of being blameless in adherence to the law.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 20, 55, 3, 5, 5, 'all these have I observed', 'Observance vs. True Power', 'This connection highlights the contrast between mere observance of the law, as indicated by ''all these have I observed,'' and the deeper, transformative power of godliness that is denied in 2 Timothy. Both passages emphasize the importance of genuine faith over superficial adherence.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 20, 40, 19, 20, 20, 'from my youth', 'Young Man''s Observance of Law', 'Both passages emphasize the young man''s claim of having kept the commandments from his youth. This connection highlights the consistency in his response to Jesus regarding his adherence to the law.', 'parallel', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 20, 42, 18, 11, 12, 'all these have I observed', 'Self-Righteousness in Prayer', 'Both passages emphasize the self-assuredness of individuals regarding their adherence to the law. The rich young ruler claims, ''all these have I observed,'' while the Pharisee expresses gratitude for his own righteousness.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 20, 45, 7, 9, 9, 'all these have I observed', 'Connection of Law and Sin', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between adherence to the law and the awareness of sin. In Mark, the individual claims to have observed the commandments, while in Romans, the arrival of the commandment brings awareness of sin''s impact.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 20, 23, 58, 2, 2, NULL, 'Seeking God and Righteousness', 'This connection highlights the theme of seeking God and observing His ways. Both passages emphasize a commitment to righteousness and a desire to know God''s ordinances.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 21, 40, 6, 19, 21, 'treasure in heaven', 'Connection of Treasures in Heaven', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of prioritizing treasures in heaven over earthly possessions. Jesus instructs the rich man to give to the poor, aligning with the call to lay up treasures in heaven.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 21, 66, 2, 4, 4, 'loved him', 'Love and Commitment to God', 'This connection highlights the theme of love and commitment in both passages. In Mark, Jesus emphasizes the need to follow Him and prioritize spiritual wealth, while Revelation addresses the loss of ''first love,'' indicating a departure from that commitment.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 21, 42, 18, 22, 22, 'sell whatsoever thou hast, and give to the poor', 'Connection of Jesus'' Call to Discipleship', 'Both passages emphasize the necessity of selling possessions and giving to the poor as a prerequisite for following Jesus. They highlight the idea of gaining treasure in heaven through selflessness and commitment to discipleship.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 21, 42, 10, 42, 42, 'one thing thou lackest', 'Importance of Choosing the Good Part', 'Both passages emphasize the necessity of prioritizing spiritual wealth over material possessions. In Mark, Jesus instructs the rich man to sell all he has, while in Luke, Mary is commended for choosing what is ''needful.''', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 21, 44, 2, 45, 45, 'sell whatsoever thou hast, and give to the poor', 'Connection of Generosity and Discipleship', 'This connection highlights the theme of selling possessions and giving to the poor. Both passages emphasize the call to share resources for the benefit of others, reflecting a commitment to community and discipleship.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 21, 54, 6, 17, 19, 'give to the poor', 'Connection of Wealth and Eternal Life', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of using wealth for good works and the pursuit of eternal life. Mark 10:21 speaks of selling possessions and giving to the poor, while 1 Timothy 6:18 encourages being rich in good works and willing to distribute.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 21, 40, 16, 24, 24, 'take up the cross, and follow me', 'Call to Discipleship', 'Both passages emphasize the necessity of taking up the cross and following Jesus. They highlight the commitment required for discipleship, including self-denial and prioritizing spiritual over material wealth.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 22, 62, 2, 15, 16, 'great possessions', 'Attachment to Material Possessions', 'This connection highlights the theme of attachment to worldly possessions. In Mark 10:22, the man''s sadness over his great possessions parallels the warning in 1 John 2:15-16 against loving the world and its desires.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
